1
00:00:04,137 --> 00:00:06,037
I'm reckless because I'm a kid.

2
00:00:06,037 --> 00:00:07,570
[Episode 12]
Should I just whisk you off so that

3
00:00:07,570 --> 00:00:09,271
you don't have to play Miss Devoted?

4
00:00:10,370 --> 00:00:11,403
Are you nuts?

5
00:00:11,403 --> 00:00:14,937
Even if I were to give up,
why would you whisk me off?

6
00:00:14,937 --> 00:00:17,837
It was me who encouraged
you to get married.

7
00:00:17,837 --> 00:00:21,071
Since you want out because it's hard,
I should be held accountable.

8
00:00:21,071 --> 00:00:23,737
If you keep that ring on though,
I won't go against my word.

9
00:00:23,737 --> 00:00:28,271
But if you do take off that ring,
I'll take that as a green light

10
00:00:28,271 --> 00:00:30,503
to whisk you off.

11
00:00:31,403 --> 00:00:33,637
I'm not threatening you to take off
the ring right away.

12
00:00:33,637 --> 00:00:37,370
But I won't encourage you
to keep that ring on either.

13
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:41,470
Just think of it as a proposal
to keep you from crying again.

14
00:00:41,470 --> 00:00:43,271
You call that a proposal?

15
00:00:43,271 --> 00:00:45,171
How can I ever agree to it?

16
00:00:45,171 --> 00:00:46,971
My proposal's on the table.

17
00:00:46,971 --> 00:00:49,238
You won't have a lot of time
to mull this over

18
00:00:49,238 --> 00:00:51,338
as the switchover might happen soon.

19
00:00:51,338 --> 00:00:54,837
I won't break my promise that I'll go
away as soon I return to my body,

20
00:00:54,837 --> 00:00:58,870
so if you want to see Kang Gyeong Jun,
take off the ring.

21
00:01:06,870 --> 00:01:09,604
You said you couldn't go up
and see Seo Yun Jae's mother.

22
00:01:09,604 --> 00:01:10,937
Let's go.

23
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:30,937
Why are you sneaking glances of me?
You can look at me if you want to.

24
00:01:33,870 --> 00:01:38,304
How can you be so unaffected
after making such a proposal?

25
00:01:38,304 --> 00:01:41,071
I'm fine because I have no expectations.

26
00:01:41,071 --> 00:01:43,104
You're not going to take off
the ring, are you?

27
00:01:44,271 --> 00:01:46,904
Are you wavering?

28
00:01:50,137 --> 00:01:53,737
If you start wavering, I'll
start getting serious, too.

29
00:01:54,971 --> 00:01:57,137
Why would I waver?

30
00:01:57,137 --> 00:01:59,837
At least you're not calling me
a nursling anymore.

31
00:01:59,837 --> 00:02:02,304
If you called me that, I was
going to take it all back.

32
00:02:03,037 --> 00:02:04,704
Does this mean you don't
want me to take it back?

33
00:02:04,704 --> 00:02:07,403
How can you be joking around

34
00:02:07,403 --> 00:02:08,637
after what you just said?

35
00:02:08,637 --> 00:02:11,037
So this means you're taking this seriously.

36
00:02:11,037 --> 00:02:12,403
Are you really wavering?

37
00:02:12,403 --> 00:02:14,071
No.

38
00:02:14,071 --> 00:02:16,737
So what does it matter if I joke around?

39
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:24,904
He's at the hospital.

40
00:02:26,037 --> 00:02:28,304
He's in a coma.

41
00:02:29,637 --> 00:02:30,971
So?

42
00:02:30,971 --> 00:02:33,971
He saved Yun Jae's life.

43
00:02:35,171 --> 00:02:37,737
We can't turn our backs on him.

44
00:02:39,104 --> 00:02:44,670
Yun Jae saved his life.

45
00:02:44,670 --> 00:02:47,637
They were in the same accident,

46
00:02:47,637 --> 00:02:50,637
and Yun Jae saved him.

47
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:55,804
The debt has been settled, hasn't it?

48
00:02:57,304 --> 00:02:59,770
Does this mean

49
00:02:59,770 --> 00:03:03,804
you knew he was in the hospital?

50
00:03:04,537 --> 00:03:08,537
Yun Jae's been trying to find his father.

51
00:03:08,537 --> 00:03:11,071
Of course, I told him I didn't know anything.

52
00:03:11,071 --> 00:03:13,004
Are you going to tell Yun Jae everything

53
00:03:13,004 --> 00:03:16,971
and make me out to be the bad person?

54
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:24,304
Are you suggesting that we
abandon Gyeong Jun again?

55
00:03:25,137 --> 00:03:26,704
I can't do that.

56
00:03:26,704 --> 00:03:28,971
You must choose.

57
00:03:29,338 --> 00:03:32,304
You once left that woman and the kid

58
00:03:32,304 --> 00:03:35,171
to be with me and Yun Jae.

59
00:03:35,171 --> 00:03:37,104
Who will it be this time?

60
00:03:37,104 --> 00:03:41,137
Will it be Yun Jae and me
or Kang Gyeong Jun?

61
00:03:41,770 --> 00:03:43,804
Let me make this clear.

62
00:03:43,804 --> 00:03:47,971
If you choose him, you won't
ever see Yun Jae and me again.

63
00:03:55,937 --> 00:03:57,704
Gil Teacher,

64
00:03:57,704 --> 00:03:59,937
don't hold onto to the ring like that.

65
00:03:59,937 --> 00:04:03,104
I won't whisk you off just because
you don't have your ring on.

66
00:04:05,770 --> 00:04:07,904
That's not why I'm wearing the ring!

67
00:04:13,537 --> 00:04:16,537
Did you wash your hair with the ring on?

68
00:04:16,537 --> 00:04:19,071
I won't whisk you off just because
you don't have your ring on.

69
00:04:19,071 --> 00:04:21,004
That's not why I kept it on.

70
00:04:35,204 --> 00:04:37,104
Is something bothering you?

71
00:04:37,470 --> 00:04:39,770
No.

72
00:04:39,770 --> 00:04:42,837
I'd be nuts to take a kid's joke seriously.

73
00:04:43,670 --> 00:04:45,437
Whatever it is, you're taking it seriously.

74
00:04:45,437 --> 00:04:48,338
You've been staring at your ring all day.

75
00:04:48,338 --> 00:04:50,870
Did you and Yun Jae get into an argument?

76
00:04:52,670 --> 00:04:54,137
Ae Gyeong, let's say

77
00:04:54,837 --> 00:05:00,071
a devoted wife doesn't know
when her husband will be back.

78
00:05:00,071 --> 00:05:02,204
What can she do to keep
herself from falling for

79
00:05:02,204 --> 00:05:03,770
the guy next door?

80
00:05:08,870 --> 00:05:11,271
You need to keep a silver dagger nearby.

81
00:05:11,271 --> 00:05:13,403
I have a silver dagger.

82
00:05:13,403 --> 00:05:16,971
You're done for if you approach me.

83
00:05:17,971 --> 00:05:19,637
Right?

84
00:05:19,637 --> 00:05:22,403
You shouldn't let go of
the silver dagger, right?

85
00:05:22,837 --> 00:05:25,570
But the best way is to keep
the guy next door out of your sight.

86
00:05:26,104 --> 00:05:31,071
You should either kick the guy out
or move to another house.

87
00:05:31,704 --> 00:05:38,470
You're right. It's best just
not to be around him.

88
00:05:39,770 --> 00:05:44,338
Hey. Is that contract teaching position
still available in Chuncheon?

89
00:05:44,338 --> 00:05:46,537
They found someone ages ago.

90
00:05:46,537 --> 00:05:47,837
Why do you ask?

91
00:05:47,837 --> 00:05:52,338
Aren't you going to stay here until
you get your official appointment?

92
00:05:52,338 --> 00:05:55,737
I was just curious.

93
00:06:03,104 --> 00:06:05,104
You can take off your precious ring.

94
00:06:05,670 --> 00:06:08,503
I won't whisk you off just because
you don't have your ring on.

95
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:10,737
Let me know when you're done.

96
00:06:10,737 --> 00:06:12,637
I can put the laces on for you.

97
00:06:16,604 --> 00:06:18,204
Kang Gyeong Jun,

98
00:06:18,204 --> 00:06:21,937
how can you joke around after
putting me in this predicament?

99
00:06:22,570 --> 00:06:24,737
Having you deal with a predicament

100
00:06:24,737 --> 00:06:26,570
is better than seeing you depressed.

101
00:06:27,737 --> 00:06:31,271
I can't play along with your
childish games right now.

102
00:06:31,271 --> 00:06:35,670
Would you rather be an adult and bear it all?

103
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:37,570
I'm just curious.

104
00:06:37,570 --> 00:06:39,804
What is it that you're bearing?

105
00:06:39,804 --> 00:06:41,470
What do you find so hard to put up with?

106
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:42,770
Is it Seo Yun Jae who you miss

107
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:44,637
or is it his mother who's a show off?

108
00:06:44,637 --> 00:06:46,704
Or is it his unapproachable father?

109
00:06:47,804 --> 00:06:49,704
It's you.

110
00:06:50,837 --> 00:06:52,338
- Me?
- That's right.

111
00:06:52,338 --> 00:06:54,171
I find you the most difficult to bear.

112
00:06:54,171 --> 00:06:55,704
Why me?

113
00:06:55,704 --> 00:06:56,971
I've been so good to you.

114
00:06:56,971 --> 00:07:00,071
Yup. Having a great time with you

115
00:07:00,071 --> 00:07:03,604
while I'm supposed to be waiting for Yun Jae
has been the hardest to bear.

116
00:07:03,604 --> 00:07:05,403
I've been hard to bear?

117
00:07:05,403 --> 00:07:07,637
What would you have done
if I were even nicer to you?

118
00:07:07,637 --> 00:07:08,804
You would've keeled over.

119
00:07:08,804 --> 00:07:11,171
In any case, it was wrong of me.

120
00:07:11,171 --> 00:07:14,837
I should've known better, and I won't
be like that any more.

121
00:07:14,837 --> 00:07:17,470
You won't need me once
you find your father, right?

122
00:07:17,470 --> 00:07:20,171
Let's go our separate ways
once you find your father.

123
00:07:20,171 --> 00:07:21,503
You don't have to feel responsible for me.

124
00:07:21,503 --> 00:07:24,704
Fine. I'm glad we won't need each other.

125
00:07:24,704 --> 00:07:27,637
Yup. Let's part ways for good.

126
00:07:33,804 --> 00:07:38,104
She's trying to sever her ties with me
now that Yun Jae's about to return.

127
00:08:32,104 --> 00:08:33,770
So she's started, eh?

128
00:08:33,770 --> 00:08:35,437
I should start too then.

129
00:08:51,304 --> 00:08:52,704
Gil Da Ran,

130
00:08:53,837 --> 00:08:55,470
I wanted to throw out anything
that ties me to you too,

131
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:57,171
but you've never given me anything.

132
00:08:57,171 --> 00:08:58,370
See?

133
00:08:58,370 --> 00:09:01,004
You haven't done anything for me.

134
00:09:02,637 --> 00:09:03,737
And look.

135
00:09:03,737 --> 00:09:05,238
I've done so much for you.

136
00:09:05,238 --> 00:09:08,403
So this is why you've
had it so tough, right?

137
00:09:08,403 --> 00:09:10,271
What if I had given you enough
to fill up the whole bag?

138
00:09:10,271 --> 00:09:12,004
The stress would've killed you.

139
00:09:28,570 --> 00:09:31,238
I really

140
00:09:31,238 --> 00:09:34,204
haven't done anything for him.

141
00:09:52,071 --> 00:09:53,637
These are all going.

142
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:35,837
The flowers will wilt eventually.

143
00:10:36,704 --> 00:10:39,604
I'll just keep them until then.

144
00:10:53,971 --> 00:10:57,470
Why are you looking at me like that?
I'm going to throw you out.

145
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:16,503
I might go to China at some point.

146
00:11:27,937 --> 00:11:29,704
The Great Wall of China.

147
00:11:36,804 --> 00:11:43,071
He's even taken me to the Great Wall.

148
00:12:49,137 --> 00:12:51,338
Gyeong Jun,

149
00:12:54,271 --> 00:12:56,071
I'm sorry.

150
00:13:09,770 --> 00:13:12,004
I like you.

151
00:13:33,737 --> 00:13:37,604
My dad hasn't heard back from him, either.

152
00:13:38,104 --> 00:13:39,837
Why isn't he coming?

153
00:13:39,837 --> 00:13:42,670
I think it was the guy
who came by the other day.

154
00:13:43,604 --> 00:13:47,904
So he came for a quick visit and that's it?

155
00:13:47,904 --> 00:13:50,670
Will we not be able to find him
if he doesn't call again?

156
00:13:51,171 --> 00:13:54,570
It would be his loss.

157
00:13:54,570 --> 00:13:56,704
I'll soon be returning to
my body and waking up.

158
00:13:56,704 --> 00:13:59,837
He would then be losing a smart, rich,

159
00:13:59,837 --> 00:14:01,204
and very well-behaved son.

160
00:14:01,204 --> 00:14:03,870
That's right. It'd be his loss.

161
00:14:04,737 --> 00:14:06,971
Don't tell Gil Teacher.

162
00:14:06,971 --> 00:14:09,971
She can't wait for me to find my father
so that she can get rid of me.

163
00:14:09,971 --> 00:14:11,437
She'll be disappointed.

164
00:14:11,437 --> 00:14:13,338
She's cleaned me out of her life already.

165
00:14:14,238 --> 00:14:15,837
Gyeong Jun,

166
00:14:15,837 --> 00:14:18,604
it's okay even if you don't find your father.

167
00:14:18,604 --> 00:14:22,403
Once you return to your body,
we can go back to the States.

168
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:23,704
Once my birthday comes around,

169
00:14:23,704 --> 00:14:27,271
I'll be fine living alone wherever.

170
00:14:27,271 --> 00:14:30,770
I'm going to sever my ties
and take off then.

171
00:14:32,171 --> 00:14:33,470
You startled me.

172
00:14:33,971 --> 00:14:36,737
Shouldn't we find out how much money

173
00:14:36,737 --> 00:14:39,037
Gyeong Jun will be coming into?

174
00:14:39,037 --> 00:14:41,071
Why don't you call the States?

175
00:14:42,137 --> 00:14:46,271
I'll look into into it after his birthday.

176
00:14:47,637 --> 00:14:49,238
Good grief.

177
00:14:52,338 --> 00:14:54,470
You've reached Miracle.

178
00:14:55,837 --> 00:14:58,071
A reservation?

179
00:14:58,071 --> 00:14:59,238
Sure.

180
00:14:59,238 --> 00:15:01,104
Of course.

181
00:15:01,104 --> 00:15:04,403
Yes.

182
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:07,470
For two. Great.

183
00:15:07,470 --> 00:15:10,204
You can make your selections
once you get here.

184
00:15:10,204 --> 00:15:11,704
Yes.

185
00:15:11,704 --> 00:15:14,704
We'll have a nice table ready for you.

186
00:15:15,204 --> 00:15:20,271
Kang Gyeong Jun's friends
are looking for his father.

187
00:15:20,271 --> 00:15:22,804
I thought you should know.

188
00:15:22,804 --> 00:15:25,637
That side's searching, too?

189
00:15:28,570 --> 00:15:30,437
By the way, do you know

190
00:15:30,437 --> 00:15:35,570
if Da Ran was seeing someone
after calling off the first wedding?

191
00:15:35,971 --> 00:15:38,437
I don't know. Why do you ask?

192
00:15:38,437 --> 00:15:44,503
She came to see me and suddenly
said she didn't deserve Yun Jae.

193
00:15:44,503 --> 00:15:49,904
It seemed like she really meant it.
She appeared to be feeling guilty.

194
00:15:49,904 --> 00:15:53,171
She did come to me too,

195
00:15:53,171 --> 00:15:55,370
and she seemed troubled.

196
00:15:56,271 --> 00:15:57,837
Really?

197
00:15:57,837 --> 00:16:03,004
Yun Jae is looking out for her
more than he ever used to,

198
00:16:03,004 --> 00:16:05,904
so I don't know what could
possibly be bothering her.

199
00:16:06,537 --> 00:16:10,204
I want the old Yun Jae back,
but Da Ran says

200
00:16:10,204 --> 00:16:15,570
she will only stick around
for the current Yun Jae.

201
00:16:15,570 --> 00:16:19,804
That makes me even more wary of her.

202
00:16:20,704 --> 00:16:23,071
I figured you wouldn't come.

203
00:16:23,071 --> 00:16:25,770
I have to go because it's
an annual family event.

204
00:16:25,770 --> 00:16:28,437
I'll tell them you had to go
to a colleague's wedding.

205
00:16:28,437 --> 00:16:30,804
If they call, I'll tell them I'm home.

206
00:16:32,737 --> 00:16:35,037
I'm taking your car.

207
00:16:36,338 --> 00:16:38,971
Should I have kept these
in the freezer longer?

208
00:16:41,171 --> 00:16:45,271
I should cool down the car for you, right?

209
00:16:45,341 --> 00:16:50,405
[Remote Engine Start
Temperature Settings: High]

210
00:17:06,137 --> 00:17:08,304
It's so hot. What's going on?

211
00:17:10,370 --> 00:17:14,770
I should have turned on the AC,
but I guess hit the heater button.

212
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:19,870
It's like a dry sauna in there.

213
00:17:26,071 --> 00:17:27,937
Leave the car here.

214
00:17:32,137 --> 00:17:34,704
It's my parents. Go on in
so they don't see you.

215
00:17:34,704 --> 00:17:36,037
Why should I?

216
00:17:36,037 --> 00:17:39,271
I'm not cooperating. It's not like
I'll be seeing them again anyway.

217
00:17:39,971 --> 00:17:41,670
I should turn on the AC.

218
00:17:49,704 --> 00:17:51,837
I'm all ready. Let's go.

219
00:17:51,837 --> 00:17:53,503
You were home?

220
00:17:53,503 --> 00:17:55,370
He's on his way out to the wedding.

221
00:17:55,370 --> 00:17:56,770
Dressed like that?

222
00:17:56,770 --> 00:17:59,171
Are you going to your colleague's wedding?

223
00:17:59,171 --> 00:18:00,238
No.

224
00:18:00,238 --> 00:18:02,137
Then come camping with us.

225
00:18:02,137 --> 00:18:03,403
Come on, Yun Jae.

226
00:18:03,403 --> 00:18:05,037
I'm not coming.

227
00:18:12,604 --> 00:18:15,171
We had a fight.

228
00:18:15,171 --> 00:18:17,537
The four of us can go. I'll drive.

229
00:18:17,537 --> 00:18:18,704
Let's go, dad.

230
00:18:22,870 --> 00:18:24,804
Did I slam the door too forcefully?

231
00:18:29,271 --> 00:18:31,004
I was going to find rocks with Mr. Gil,

232
00:18:31,004 --> 00:18:33,004
and Ms. Gil said she was
making kimbap for me.

233
00:18:33,004 --> 00:18:34,804
And Chung Sik and I had plans

234
00:18:35,370 --> 00:18:37,637
to watch porn.

235
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:41,804
What a shame.

236
00:18:43,403 --> 00:18:46,238
Don't you dare call or text Yun Jae.

237
00:18:59,370 --> 00:19:00,937
I'm throwing everything out.

238
00:19:00,937 --> 00:19:03,403
This house will be free
of Gil Da Ran's things.

239
00:19:16,370 --> 00:19:18,737
This whole room has to go.

240
00:19:23,338 --> 00:19:25,104
Huh?

241
00:19:28,637 --> 00:19:30,737
She brought them back in.

242
00:19:36,171 --> 00:19:38,104
But then again,

243
00:19:38,104 --> 00:19:40,137
they're not things anyone
can part with easily.

244
00:20:18,570 --> 00:20:22,537
[Father-in-law: Yun Jae, we need
to find a son-in-law stone together]

245
00:20:23,304 --> 00:20:26,670
[Mother-in-law: Yun Jae,
guess what I put in the kimbap]

246
00:20:26,670 --> 00:20:29,004
[Come try them and then guess]

247
00:20:29,470 --> 00:20:35,004
[Brother-in-law: Yun Jae, you said
to keep one's defiance short]

248
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:37,604
Good grief.

249
00:20:37,604 --> 00:20:39,770
They all want to see me so badly,

250
00:20:39,770 --> 00:20:41,837
but why aren't they giving me directions?

251
00:20:52,171 --> 00:20:54,271
There are so many stones.

252
00:21:05,137 --> 00:21:08,637
It's pointy, rough, and shiny,

253
00:21:08,637 --> 00:21:11,304
just like Kang Gyeong Jun.

254
00:21:23,037 --> 00:21:24,238
Huh?

255
00:21:24,238 --> 00:21:26,470
