520
00:41:31,904 --> 00:41:34,137
Yeah.

521
00:41:34,137 --> 00:41:37,204
You should stop stalking
that old man and Yun Jae

522
00:41:37,204 --> 00:41:38,937
and return to the States.

523
00:41:40,238 --> 00:41:41,503
What?

524
00:41:41,503 --> 00:41:42,971
You're heading back to the States?

525
00:41:42,971 --> 00:41:44,670
Yeah.

526
00:41:44,670 --> 00:41:46,171
Me too.

527
00:41:46,171 --> 00:41:48,238
America, me too.

528
00:41:49,937 --> 00:41:53,037
Mary, America. Ame...

529
00:41:57,271 --> 00:42:00,238
[Ms. Jang Mary, this is
Gyeong Jun's father]

530
00:42:00,238 --> 00:42:01,770
[Could I meet with you?]

531
00:42:03,238 --> 00:42:05,904
Mary, wait for me.

532
00:42:06,770 --> 00:42:08,537
Mary.

533
00:42:08,537 --> 00:42:10,037
Mary.

534
00:42:11,937 --> 00:42:14,171
Your father finally got in touch with me.

535
00:42:14,171 --> 00:42:16,171
Come with me to meet him.

536
00:42:16,171 --> 00:42:20,004
Why is he so secretive?
Why did he block his number?

537
00:42:20,004 --> 00:42:23,304
Is he ashamed of me because
I'm a love child? How insulting.

538
00:42:23,304 --> 00:42:26,503
He won't know who you are, so you can
meet him without him knowing.

539
00:42:26,503 --> 00:42:29,137
Since he's gotten in touch,
I'll go and see who he is.

540
00:42:29,137 --> 00:42:31,238
Now that you've found your father,

541
00:42:31,238 --> 00:42:34,637
Ms. Gil can move on with peace of mind.

542
00:42:35,370 --> 00:42:38,338
You make it sound so simple.

543
00:42:43,870 --> 00:42:46,637
You want to transfer to
a school outside Seoul?

544
00:42:47,271 --> 00:42:49,937
My first appointment will probably
be in that area anyway,

545
00:42:49,937 --> 00:42:52,171
so it wouldn't hurt to get there now
and get myself acclimated.

546
00:42:52,171 --> 00:42:53,971
What about Yun Jae?

547
00:42:53,971 --> 00:42:57,937
Is he okay with that?
You only just got married.

548
00:42:57,937 --> 00:43:00,071
We talked it through.

549
00:43:00,804 --> 00:43:03,238
- Dad.
- Yes?

550
00:43:03,238 --> 00:43:06,204
You were 35 when mom, who was 19,

551
00:43:06,204 --> 00:43:09,870
came to you against her parents' wishes

552
00:43:09,870 --> 00:43:12,637
and asked you to marry her.

553
00:43:12,637 --> 00:43:14,503
Why did you say yes?

554
00:43:16,937 --> 00:43:18,770
Well...

555
00:43:18,770 --> 00:43:21,238
Why did I say yes...

556
00:43:21,637 --> 00:43:27,770
I had asked for a transfer to a remote island

557
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:31,171
to keep myself away from your mother.

558
00:43:31,171 --> 00:43:36,503
I did all I could not to get
involved with your mother,

559
00:43:36,503 --> 00:43:41,770
but the more I tried, the more
I fell in love with her.

560
00:43:41,770 --> 00:43:44,770
I was crying over

561
00:43:44,770 --> 00:43:48,437
how I had lost her, how I would
never be able to forget her,

562
00:43:48,437 --> 00:43:51,704
and your mom, thankfully,

563
00:43:51,704 --> 00:43:54,271
came to me just then.

564
00:43:55,704 --> 00:44:00,271
But how did you know you'd never forget her?

565
00:44:00,271 --> 00:44:02,271
Wouldn't you have only known
at the end of your life?

566
00:44:02,271 --> 00:44:04,770
That's true,

567
00:44:04,770 --> 00:44:09,870
but it would've been sad if I had
spent my entire life wondering.

568
00:44:09,870 --> 00:44:12,437
I had the courage to go for it, however,

569
00:44:12,437 --> 00:44:17,071
and I got a lifetime of happiness.

570
00:44:18,271 --> 00:44:22,037
But how did you work up the courage?

571
00:44:22,037 --> 00:44:26,338
I tossed all sense of reason into the ocean.

572
00:44:26,338 --> 00:44:29,004
And that's how

573
00:44:29,004 --> 00:44:31,370
I ended up with your mom.

574
00:44:45,937 --> 00:44:50,637
I'm at the hospital lobby where
I've arranged to meet with your dad.

575
00:44:50,637 --> 00:44:51,503
What about you?

576
00:44:51,503 --> 00:44:53,137
I'm at the hospital.

577
00:44:53,137 --> 00:44:54,704
I'll meet you at the lobby.

578
00:44:57,370 --> 00:44:58,770
Yun Jae,

579
00:45:02,537 --> 00:45:06,637
Da Ran came to see me recently.
Has she told you?

580
00:45:06,637 --> 00:45:09,137
You told her nothing had gone on between us.

581
00:45:09,937 --> 00:45:10,770
Yes.

582
00:45:10,770 --> 00:45:14,804
Has that caused any problems?

583
00:45:16,338 --> 00:45:18,937
I thought she'd be happy,

584
00:45:18,937 --> 00:45:21,037
but she was so shocked.

585
00:45:22,004 --> 00:45:24,503
I'd decided to let you go for your sake,

586
00:45:24,503 --> 00:45:26,870
but she didn't seem too
happy to hear the news.

587
00:45:26,870 --> 00:45:28,503
Maybe I shouldn't have said anything.

588
00:45:28,503 --> 00:45:31,837
She was so happy that she was moved to tears.

589
00:45:33,370 --> 00:45:37,403
Do you still check in on Kang Gyeong Jun?

590
00:45:37,937 --> 00:45:39,304
Why do you ask?

591
00:45:39,304 --> 00:45:41,604
I'm his primary care physician.

592
00:45:41,604 --> 00:45:45,870
I feel sorry for him. You should
continue to look out for him.

593
00:45:52,770 --> 00:45:55,937
Even Lee Se Yeong feels sorry for me?

594
00:45:55,937 --> 00:45:57,338
I can't wait to return my body.

595
00:46:02,437 --> 00:46:04,071
I'm here.

596
00:46:04,071 --> 00:46:05,338
I'll be right there.

597
00:46:46,503 --> 00:46:47,670
Yun Jae.

598
00:46:49,537 --> 00:46:50,670
Gyeong Jun.

599
00:46:51,370 --> 00:46:53,071
Are you okay, Yun Jae?

600
00:46:53,071 --> 00:46:54,804
Are you not feeling well?

601
00:46:56,271 --> 00:46:57,338
What's wrong?

602
00:46:57,338 --> 00:46:59,770
Dr. Seo, are you okay?

603
00:47:02,570 --> 00:47:04,204
I'm fine.

604
00:47:04,204 --> 00:47:07,004
I'm better now. It was just a dizzy spell.

605
00:47:08,904 --> 00:47:10,704
Are you sure you're okay?

606
00:47:12,137 --> 00:47:14,004
- I'm fine.
- No.

607
00:47:14,004 --> 00:47:16,470
Let's get you checked out.

608
00:47:16,470 --> 00:47:18,770
I can't leave things like this.

609
00:47:19,604 --> 00:47:21,037
Let's go.

610
00:47:25,804 --> 00:47:27,704
Did you come to see me?

611
00:47:27,704 --> 00:47:31,137
Yes, and the director of this hospital
is a friend of mine.

612
00:47:32,137 --> 00:47:38,670
Had you come to see a patient here
with mom recently?

613
00:47:38,670 --> 00:47:40,537
What are you talking about?

614
00:47:42,670 --> 00:47:45,503
I thought I saw you two.

615
00:47:46,238 --> 00:47:48,071
We were never here together.

616
00:47:50,704 --> 00:47:55,171
You don't look well. Let's get you examined.

617
00:47:58,437 --> 00:48:02,470
I know my own body best.

618
00:48:02,470 --> 00:48:06,037
I know this isn't something
that requires tests.

619
00:48:08,104 --> 00:48:11,904
Do you get dizzy spells often?

620
00:48:12,670 --> 00:48:14,370
Every now and again.

621
00:48:15,937 --> 00:48:17,870
Yun Jae,

622
00:48:18,804 --> 00:48:21,670
your mother would be very
worried if she found out.

623
00:48:21,670 --> 00:48:23,171
You may not remember,

624
00:48:23,171 --> 00:48:26,338
but you were very ill when you were little.

625
00:48:26,338 --> 00:48:28,804
If anything bothers you at all,

626
00:48:28,804 --> 00:48:30,670
you should see the doctor right away.

627
00:48:31,171 --> 00:48:32,737
Okay.

628
00:48:32,737 --> 00:48:37,204
But don't tell mom.

629
00:48:37,204 --> 00:48:38,971
It will only complicate matters.

630
00:48:41,837 --> 00:48:43,604
Okay.

631
00:48:52,437 --> 00:48:56,370
When Yun Jae's test results come out,
please notify me first.

632
00:48:56,370 --> 00:48:58,403
I don't want word getting
out at the hospital.

633
00:48:58,737 --> 00:48:59,870
Yes, Dr. Seo.

634
00:49:00,470 --> 00:49:03,004
So he had you get a whole bunch of tests?

635
00:49:04,004 --> 00:49:05,403
Yeah.

636
00:49:05,870 --> 00:49:08,704
This dude was apparently
very ill when he was little.

637
00:49:08,704 --> 00:49:11,104
His dad was really worried
he'd get sick again.

638
00:49:11,104 --> 00:49:15,704
Does it hurt when your soul
travels back and forth?

639
00:49:17,637 --> 00:49:19,104
It's ridiculously painful.

640
00:49:19,104 --> 00:49:22,704
Seo Yun Jae's father cares
a lot about his son.

641
00:49:23,338 --> 00:49:26,403
I don't know why your father never showed up.

642
00:49:27,271 --> 00:49:29,537
I've decided to give up on finding my dad.

643
00:49:30,537 --> 00:49:32,071
Just tell Ms. Gil my dad came,

644
00:49:32,071 --> 00:49:34,204
so she won't have to bother with it anymore.

645
00:49:37,004 --> 00:49:40,004
I was going to find your dad for you,

646
00:49:41,338 --> 00:49:44,071
but I guess now I'm the only one

647
00:49:44,071 --> 00:49:46,271
who will be by your side.

648
00:49:46,737 --> 00:49:49,204
You brought more of your stuff, didn't you?

649
00:49:49,204 --> 00:49:50,370
I'm throwing everything out.

650
00:49:50,370 --> 00:49:51,870
I'll take care of it.

651
00:49:51,870 --> 00:49:53,937
We should get ready to go back to the States.

652
00:50:09,171 --> 00:50:10,804
Yun Jae.

653
00:50:11,604 --> 00:50:12,403
Gyeong Jun.

654
00:50:17,503 --> 00:50:20,937
I thought he was Gyeong Jun's father,

655
00:50:21,737 --> 00:50:23,937
but he turned out to be Seo Yun Jae's father.

656
00:50:31,437 --> 00:50:35,904
I should plan a great birthday party
for Gyeong Jun to cheer him up.

657
00:50:37,437 --> 00:50:41,737
Shouldn't he have come to hold
his sick son's hand?

658
00:50:52,604 --> 00:50:56,238
Warm hands must run in the family.

659
00:51:03,204 --> 00:51:07,604
Ms. Gil, you've been working late these days.

660
00:51:07,604 --> 00:51:10,670
I have some more work to do.
I'll see you tomorrow.

661
00:51:10,670 --> 00:51:14,104
I doubt it's work. You must've
had a spat with your husband.

662
00:51:26,437 --> 00:51:28,570
June 24th.

663
00:51:29,137 --> 00:51:31,837
It'll be Gyeong Jun's birthday soon.

664
00:51:32,637 --> 00:51:35,238
Happy birthday, Gyeong Jun.

665
00:51:53,271 --> 00:51:55,204
Gyeong Jun,

666
00:51:56,104 --> 00:51:58,537
you're up!

667
00:52:07,171 --> 00:52:09,171
What are you looking at?

668
00:52:17,171 --> 00:52:19,171
Gyeong Jun.

669
00:52:25,437 --> 00:52:27,304
Gyeong Jun!

670
00:52:28,737 --> 00:52:30,537
Gyeong Jun!

671
00:52:31,370 --> 00:52:32,604
Gyeong Jun!

672
00:52:32,604 --> 00:52:33,870
What?

673
00:52:37,304 --> 00:52:39,204
Why were you yelling?

674
00:52:40,271 --> 00:52:42,637
You

675
00:52:42,637 --> 00:52:44,570
disappeared.

676
00:52:45,804 --> 00:52:48,470
Why would I disappear?

677
00:52:49,204 --> 00:52:51,937
Gyeong Jun,

678
00:52:51,937 --> 00:52:57,204
I'm fine the way things are right now,

679
00:52:58,271 --> 00:53:01,537
and I'd be fine if you were to
return to your body,

680
00:53:03,670 --> 00:53:08,403
but please don't disappear.

681
00:53:12,403 --> 00:53:15,204
You just had a bad dream.

682
00:53:15,204 --> 00:53:17,670
Why would I disappear?

683
00:53:40,904 --> 00:53:41,971
What's all this?

684
00:53:42,304 --> 00:53:44,637
I got some groceries.

685
00:53:53,037 --> 00:53:55,437
She must know tomorrow's my birthday.

686
00:53:58,230 --> 00:54:01,104
[Incoming Call: Byeong Su]
Byeong Su?

687
00:54:04,704 --> 00:54:07,537
Gil Teacher, phone.

688
00:54:07,537 --> 00:54:09,304
Should I get it for you?

689
00:54:12,403 --> 00:54:13,238
What?

690
00:54:13,238 --> 00:54:15,137
Isn't this Da Ran's cell phone?

691
00:54:15,537 --> 00:54:17,370
You must be her brother.

692
00:54:18,370 --> 00:54:20,370
I'm the man she's living with.

693
00:54:20,370 --> 00:54:22,071
Keep it short.

694
00:54:22,071 --> 00:54:26,338
Da Ran asked me about a contract
position, and one opened up.

695
00:54:26,338 --> 00:54:28,937
I also found a nice apartment
for her near the school,

696
00:54:28,937 --> 00:54:31,770
so please have her call me if
she wants to move in right away.

697
00:54:31,770 --> 00:54:33,037
Okay.

698
00:54:44,904 --> 00:54:46,637
You got a call. Call him back.

699
00:54:47,171 --> 00:54:48,537
Okay.

700
00:54:49,370 --> 00:54:51,737
I heard you met your father today.

701
00:54:51,737 --> 00:54:53,637
Mary told me.

702
00:54:54,971 --> 00:54:56,503
Yeah.

703
00:54:56,904 --> 00:54:59,238
What was he like?

704
00:55:00,737 --> 00:55:02,570
Don't worry about it.

705
00:55:02,570 --> 00:55:05,770
The more you know, the more ties
you will have to sever.

706
00:55:06,503 --> 00:55:08,004
I suppose.

707
00:55:09,104 --> 00:55:11,470
I have to see Seo Yun Jae's
parents tomorrow.

708
00:55:11,470 --> 00:55:13,004
They say it's a family gathering.

709
00:55:13,004 --> 00:55:15,403
They want it to be just the 3 of us.
What are you going to do?

710
00:55:17,004 --> 00:55:19,904
I won't go if I don't have to.

711
00:55:21,437 --> 00:55:22,937
Okay.

712
00:55:24,937 --> 00:55:26,537
Gyeong Jun,

713
00:55:30,137 --> 00:55:33,004
it's your birthday tomorrow, right?

714
00:55:33,004 --> 00:55:36,037
Do you want to have
dinner with me tomorrow?

715
00:55:36,037 --> 00:55:39,370
Is there anything you want
for your birthday?

716
00:55:40,770 --> 00:55:44,338
It just feels like I haven't
done anything for you,

717
00:55:44,338 --> 00:55:46,604
so I want to do something for you.

718
00:55:47,937 --> 00:55:49,338
I'm all set.

719
00:55:49,338 --> 00:55:51,437
Once I disappear from here, I'll be
throwing everything out anyway.

720
00:55:51,437 --> 00:55:53,370
I don't want another thing
I'll end up trashing anyway.

721
00:56:04,271 --> 00:56:06,770
I'm just really curious, so let me ask you.

722
00:56:06,770 --> 00:56:09,004
What is it that I've done so wrong?

723
00:56:09,370 --> 00:56:12,137
What have I done that you want
to get away from me?

724
00:56:12,137 --> 00:56:16,037
Is it because of what I said
about whisking you off?

725
00:56:16,037 --> 00:56:19,104
I told you I wouldn't do anything
so long as you kept your ring on.

726
00:56:19,104 --> 00:56:21,370
I just need

727
00:56:21,370 --> 00:56:23,570
an ocean I can't cross.

728
00:56:23,570 --> 00:56:24,937
An ocean?

729
00:56:24,937 --> 00:56:27,537
Are you thinking of transferring
to an island or something?

730
00:56:27,537 --> 00:56:29,271
Fine. Go.

731
00:56:29,271 --> 00:56:32,870
I hate going on ships, so you'll
never have to see me.

732
00:56:32,870 --> 00:56:35,071
Don't you ever think of leaving
that island either.

733
00:56:43,971 --> 00:56:49,137
 Happy birthday to you 

734
00:56:49,137 --> 00:56:55,004
 Happy birthday, dear prince 

735
00:56:59,437 --> 00:57:01,670
Gyeong Jun,

736
00:57:01,670 --> 00:57:04,037
come back soon

737
00:57:04,604 --> 00:57:06,737
so that you can live with me.

738
00:57:13,870 --> 00:57:15,637
Happy birthday, Gyeong Jun.

739
00:57:15,637 --> 00:57:18,503
Let's have dinner together.
I have a present for you.

740
00:57:20,670 --> 00:57:22,370
I'm not going.

741
00:57:27,937 --> 00:57:29,604
I'll take this one.

742
00:57:30,238 --> 00:57:33,238
We also do initial engravings.

743
00:57:33,238 --> 00:57:35,171
Oh, great.

744
00:57:37,570 --> 00:57:39,403
Please.

745
00:57:46,137 --> 00:57:48,171
It's Da Ran.

746
00:57:48,570 --> 00:57:50,338
Is it someone you know?

747
00:57:50,804 --> 00:57:52,704
My friend's wife.

748
00:57:53,537 --> 00:57:57,503
Does the engraving take long?
I need to give it to him today.

749
00:57:57,503 --> 00:57:58,804
It won't take long.

750
00:57:58,804 --> 00:58:01,470
Is it a birthday present
for your boyfriend?

751
00:58:01,470 --> 00:58:02,637
Yes.

752
00:58:02,637 --> 00:58:04,370
He's going love it.

753
00:58:04,370 --> 00:58:05,338
Birthday?

754
00:58:05,338 --> 00:58:07,870
Why don't you look around
while we get the engraving done?

755
00:58:07,870 --> 00:58:09,470
Okay.

756
00:58:22,370 --> 00:58:26,104
Those aren't Yun Jae's initials.

757
00:58:58,937 --> 00:59:03,171
I don't have the courage to toss
my sense of reason into the ocean.

758
00:59:04,304 --> 00:59:05,637
Hey,

759
00:59:06,271 --> 00:59:07,804
it's that woman from earlier.

760
00:59:07,804 --> 00:59:10,570
What's she doing taking
off her wedding ring?

761
00:59:11,338 --> 00:59:13,171
Do you think she might be having an affair?

762
00:59:14,704 --> 00:59:17,338
He won't catch on, will he?

763
00:59:28,403 --> 00:59:30,904
Gyeong Jun's father was here?

764
00:59:30,904 --> 00:59:32,104
Yes.

765
00:59:32,104 --> 00:59:34,137
He says he's taking Gyeong Jun.

766
00:59:34,503 --> 00:59:35,470
Where to?

767
00:59:35,470 --> 00:59:37,071
He probably wants his privacy,

768
00:59:37,071 --> 00:59:41,204
so we shouldn't pry.

769
00:59:41,204 --> 00:59:45,403
In any case, it's a good thing for Gyeong Jun

770
00:59:45,403 --> 00:59:49,104
that his father showed up
and wants to take care of him.

771
00:59:50,704 --> 00:59:54,437
But his father can't

772
00:59:54,437 --> 00:59:56,737
just take him away.

773
00:59:58,071 --> 01:00:02,304
The illness Dr. Seo suffered from
as a child has returned.

774
01:00:02,937 --> 01:00:07,238
Find that hematopoietic stem cell donor.

775
01:00:07,238 --> 01:00:11,004
Do you know who the donor is?

776
01:00:12,037 --> 01:00:13,770
I do.

777
01:00:27,937 --> 01:00:29,770
What is it that you have to tell me?

778
01:00:30,870 --> 01:00:32,870
It's about Da Ran.

779
01:00:32,870 --> 01:00:34,804
What?

780
01:00:34,804 --> 01:00:38,271
She was buying a birthday gift for a guy.

781
01:00:38,271 --> 01:00:41,037
I saw her at the mall.

782
01:00:41,037 --> 01:00:43,137
A birthday present?

783
01:00:43,137 --> 01:00:48,171
She was getting it engraved,
but they weren't your initials.

784
01:00:48,770 --> 01:00:50,770
So?

785
01:00:51,770 --> 01:00:55,037
She was telling the sales lady
the gift was for her boyfriend.

786
01:00:55,037 --> 01:01:00,037
She took off the wedding ring
as she waited for him.

787
01:01:02,437 --> 01:01:03,604
The ring?

788
01:01:03,604 --> 01:01:06,370
I was with a friend and she saw it too.

789
01:01:06,370 --> 01:01:08,737
She said Da Ran's definitely
having an affair.

790
01:01:10,937 --> 01:01:14,004
Da Ran looked so happy
as she was waiting for him,

791
01:01:14,004 --> 01:01:17,904
but she got very dejected
when he didn't show up.

792
01:01:18,271 --> 01:01:19,304
Really?

793
01:01:19,304 --> 01:01:21,437
Your mother said

794
01:01:21,437 --> 01:01:24,704
Da Ran had said she'd let you go
once you returned to your old self.

795
01:01:24,704 --> 01:01:27,403
Let go of Seo Yun Jae?

796
01:01:27,403 --> 01:01:29,770
She said she was having a hard time.

797
01:01:30,304 --> 01:01:33,604
No wonder. She's in love with someone else.

798
01:01:35,137 --> 01:01:36,937
Really?

799
01:01:37,304 --> 01:01:40,437
I didn't see the guy's face,

800
01:01:40,437 --> 01:01:42,537
but I know his initials.

801
01:01:43,770 --> 01:01:45,770
Do you want me to tell you?

802
01:01:47,171 --> 01:01:50,904
KKJ.

803
01:01:52,637 --> 01:01:54,570
Why are you smiling?

804
01:01:54,570 --> 01:01:57,004
Do you think I'm lying?

805
01:01:57,937 --> 01:01:59,304
No.

806
01:02:01,238 --> 01:02:03,137
You're not making this up, right?

807
01:02:03,137 --> 01:02:04,770
Of course not.

808
01:02:06,037 --> 01:02:07,704
You're sure, right?

809
01:02:07,704 --> 01:02:09,670
I'm sure.

810
01:02:13,338 --> 01:02:15,971
You're done for, Gil Da Ran.

811
01:02:44,171 --> 01:02:48,004
I need to get my sense of reason back.

812
01:02:50,104 --> 01:02:51,604
Gil Da Ran.

813
01:02:59,470 --> 01:03:01,171
Gil Da Ran,

814
01:03:01,704 --> 01:03:04,403
are you having an affair?

815
01:03:04,403 --> 01:03:05,804
What?

816
01:03:05,804 --> 01:03:08,704
Is that why you've been
having such a hard time?

817
01:03:09,971 --> 01:03:14,637
Are his initials KKJ?

818
01:03:15,570 --> 01:03:18,637
Is it Kang Gyeong Jun?

819
01:03:21,338 --> 01:03:23,537
Don't.

820
01:03:35,171 --> 01:03:38,570
The wind has blown,

821
01:03:38,570 --> 01:03:42,370
and the ship has already crossed the ocean.

822
01:03:44,537 --> 01:03:46,837
What now?
